Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.34,0:01:52.01,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Red Foot Zeff! - OG}Red Leg Zeff.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.63,0:01:55.14,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{So you are alive... - OG}You're alive.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.14,0:01:59.60,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{An incomparable pirate who was\Na cook and yet also a captain... - OG}{You served as a cook and a captain...\NAn unrivaled pirate. - Gaijin}{You were a cook and a captain,\Na pirate unlike any other. - Removed "served" because it didn't seem appropriate, but please correct if translation demands it. -JT}No pirate could compare to you,\Nbeing both a cook and a captain...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.10,0:02:02.81,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{So what if I'm alive? - OG}I'm alive. So what?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.81,0:02:05.48,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{It has nothing to do with you. - OG}It's none of your concern.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.48,0:02:10.07,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{As you can see, I live as a cook now. - OG}{As you can see, I spend\Nmy days as a chef now. - Gaijin}As you can see, I'm passing\Nmy time as a cook now.{PP/Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.90,0:02:15.70,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{If you put it that way, it sounds nice... - OG}It sounds better\Nwhen you say it like that...{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.70,0:02:19.54,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{...though rather than living as a cook, - OG}but you're not just\Npassing time as a cook.{Gab/Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.54,0:02:22.71,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{it looks like you can live only as a cook. - OG}{I doubt you could survive\Nas anything[/i1]but[/i0]a cook. - Gaijin}it looks like you can {\i1}only{\i0}\Npass your time as a cook.{Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.12,0:02:30.21,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Red Leg Zeff was a master of kicks\Nwho never used his hands in battle.{OG}{Red Leg Zeff was known as a master of kicks who never used his hands in a fight. - Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.63,0:02:37.97,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I hear that his strong legs crushed bedrock and even left footprints on steel. - OG}{His mighty legs were said to shatter bedrock and leave their mark even in steel. - Gaijin}{\q2}His mighty legs were said to shatter\Nbedrock and even leave footprints on steel.{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.76,0:02:40.68,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{And Red Foot referred to your shoes, - OG}And "Red Leg" referred to your boots,{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.68,0:02:46.69,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1982)}{which were covered in the blood that spattered as you kicked your enemies down... - OG}{which were washed in the blood of those you kicked into submission. - Gaijin}washed in the blood of those\Nyou kicked into submission.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.44,0:02:52.44,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{But you no longer have\Nthat precious leg of yours... - OG}{But it looks like you have lost\None of your esteemed legs. - Gaijin}{But it looks like you've lost\None of your esteemed legs. - Z}But you seem to have lost\None of your precious legs...{WF/Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.49,0:02:56.20,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I've heard the rumor... - OG}{Seems the rumors were true. - Gaijin}I guess the rumors were true.{WF}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.20,0:02:59.53,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{How unlucky for you to\Nhave an accident at sea... - OG}{I guess it was a stroke of bad luck\Nfor you to meet an accident at sea. - Gaijin}A stroke of bad luck\Ndoomed you to an accident at sea.{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.08,0:03:06.25,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{To you, losing one of your legs\Nmust mean you are unable to fight. - OG}I suppose losing a leg would mean\Nyou've lost the ability to fight.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.58,0:03:08.92,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{What about fighting? - OG}I don't give a damn about fighting.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.92,0:03:13.67,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I can cook without a leg\Nas long as I have these hands. - OG}I may have lost a leg, but I can cook\Nso long as I have these two hands.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.67,0:03:17.47,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{What're you trying to say?\NJust come right out and say it! - OG}{You need to get\Nto the damn point already. - Gaijin}Whatever it is, get to\Nthe damn point already!{Z/WF}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.14,0:03:21.18,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Red Foot Zeff. - OG}Red Leg Zeff,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.18,0:03:26.48,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{You're the man who once entered\Nthe Grand Line and came back unhurt... - OG}you once sailed the Grand Line\Nand returned unscathed.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.48,0:03:32.57,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{There should be a logbook with the full year of your journey chronicled in it... - OG}You must have the logbook\Nfrom that year-long voyage.{Gaijin/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.98,0:03:34.36,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Give that to me! - OG}Hand it over!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.95,0:03:40.16,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Whoa! You've been to the Grand Line, too, pops? - OG}Wow, Boss Man!\NYou sailed the Grand Line, too?!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.16,0:03:41.16,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Yeah... - OG}{A lifetime ago. - Gaijin}I did...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.99,0:03:43.66,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,My logbook, huh?{OG}{The ship's log? - Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.66,0:03:47.21,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Indeed, I have it with me. - OG}{I've got the ship's log, sure. - Gaijin}Sure, I've got what you're looking for.{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.62,0:03:50.29,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{But I can't give it to you. - OG}{But there's no way\NI'm giving it to you. - Gaijin}But there's no way in hell\NI'm giving it to you.{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.50,0:03:56.72,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{The logbook is the pride of all\Nthe crewmen that I traveled with. - OG}That logbook is the pride\Nof all those who sailed with me.{Gaijin/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.72,0:04:01.26,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{It's too important to give it to you. - OG}{It'd be a bit too weighty\Nfor the likes of you. - Gaijin}The likes of you\Ncouldn't even handle it.{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.72,0:04:04.31,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Then, I'll just take it from you by force. - OG}Then I'll just have to take it!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.06,0:04:08.56,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{It's true that I fell from the Grand Line. - OG}I admit the Grand Line\Ngot the better of me.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.56,0:04:12.32,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Even if that's the case, I'm still\NDon Krieg, the strongest man. - OG}{But even in defeat,\Nthe indomitable Don Krieg - Gaijin}{I may have faced defeat there,\Nbut the indomitable Don Krieg... - Z}That being said, I'm still\Nthe indomitable Don Krieg...{Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.98,0:04:16.99,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{It's merely a dark sea route.\NTo sail across it, I had enough power... - OG}{is plenty capable of crossing\Neven the most treacherous seas. - Gaijin}and I had the power necessary\Nto cross such a treacherous sea.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.99,0:04:18.20,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{and forces... - OG}I had the men.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.20,0:04:19.66,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{as well as ambition! - OG}I had the ambition.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.49,0:04:25.41,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{The only thing that was regrettable\Nwas that I lacked information. - OG}The only thing I lacked\Nwas information.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.87,0:04:28.12,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I just didn't know things... - OG}I just didn't know what to expect.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.21,0:04:31.63,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I'll take your logbook. - OG}{I will have that ship's log. - Gaijin}I {\i1}will{\i0} have that logbook.{JT/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.63,0:04:37.34,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{And I'll form a large pirate fleet\Nagain and seize the One Piece. - OG}With it, I will reassemble\Nmy pirate fleet, seize the One Piece,{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.76,0:04:41.14,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{And then, I'll stand on top in this Great Pirate Era! - OG}and rise to the top\Nof this Great Pirate Era!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.77,0:04:47.85,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Hold on a second! - OG}Wait just a minute.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.23,0:04:50.60,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I'm the one who's gonna be King of the Pirates! - OG}{I'm going to be the Pirate King! - Gaijin}{[/i1]I'm[/i0]going to be the Pirate King! - JT}{\i1}I'm{\i0} gonna be King of the Pirates!{WF}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.60,0:04:52.27,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Chore boy! - OG}Cabin Boy?!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.52,0:04:56.03,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Hey, back off, chore boy! - OG}Hey, back down, Cabin Boy!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.03,0:04:57.90,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{You're no match for him! - OG}You're no match for him!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.90,0:05:00.61,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I can't back off on this. - OG}I can't back down. Not about this.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.53,0:05:05.16,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Did you say something, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.66,0:05:08.00,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I can let it pass... - OG}We can pretend\NI didn't hear you say that.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.00,0:05:10.08,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{You don't have to. - OG}No need to pretend.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.08,0:05:12.00,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I just stated a fact. - OG}{I'm only saying what'll happen. - Gaijin}I'm only stating the facts.{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.79,0:05:15.00,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{This isn't a game. - OG}{This ain't a game, boy. - Gaijin}This is no game, boy.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.50,0:05:16.63,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Of course not.{OG}{You're right. - Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.63,0:05:18.97,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I'll conquer the Grand Line. - OG}I {\i1}will{\i0} conquer the Grand Line.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.76,0:05:21.76,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,It's no joke, you brat!{OG}{Don't make light of that, punk! - Gaijin}{You're taking it too lightly, punk! - JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.76,0:05:23.89,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{It's true that we didn't have information, - OG}Putting aside what we didn't know,{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.89,0:05:27.85,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{but a fleet with 5,000 men was wiped out in just seven days! That's a devilish sea! - OG}our fleet of 5,000 sailors only lasted\Nseven days on that devilish sea!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.85,0:05:30.06,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{There's no way someone\Nlike you can sail across it! - OG}A kid like you doesn't stand a chance!{Gab/Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.06,0:05:32.06,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,S-Seven days?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.06,0:05:34.94,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Krieg's pirate ships were\Nwiped out in just seven days?! - OG}{The Krieg Pirates lasted\Nonly seven days?! - Gaijin}The Krieg Pirates only\Nlasted seven days?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.61,0:05:37.28,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{What on earth happened? - OG}{What in the world\Nhappened to them?! - Gaijin}What the hell happened to them?!{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.86,0:05:42.03,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Unfortunately, I don't find\Nthose kinds of jokes funny. - OG}{I'm sorry, but I hate\Njoking around like this. - Gaijin}I'm sorry, but I hate it\Nwhen people joke around like this.{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.53,0:05:47.49,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{If you're not going to let it drop, then how about I just crush you here... - OG}{If you insist with your claim,\NI'll just crush you right here and now. - Gaijin}If you persist, I'll just\Ncrush you right here and now.{JT/Gab}{If you keep it up, I'll just\Ncrush you right here and now. - Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.91,0:05:49.87,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Go ahead if you can... - OG}If you can.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.50,0:05:54.33,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Fine by me. - OG}Perfect.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.33,0:05:58.38,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{As you wish, I'll send you to the netherworld. - OG}{I'll send you to the afterlife,\Njust as you wish. - Gaijin}As you wish, I'll be\Nsending you to the afterlife.{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.22,0:06:06.93,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Gonna fight, Luffy? Need a hand?{OG}{You gonna fight, Luffy?\NNeed some help? - Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.93,0:06:09.47,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I-If you don't need help,\Nthough, th-that's fine too... - OG}{I-I don't mind if you want\Nto fight him yourself. - Gaijin}{I-I'd also let you\Nfight him yourself, though. - JT}A-And if you don't need help,\Nth-that's fine too...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.14,0:06:13.14,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Zoro! Usopp! You stopped by? - OG}{Zoro? Usopp? I didn't\Nknow you were here! - Gaijin}Zoro! Usopp! I didn't see you there!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.14,0:06:15.23,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Don't worry. Just watch from there. - OG}I'm fine. Just watch from there.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.23,0:06:16.52,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Y-Yeah? - OG}{O-Okay. - Gaijin}I-If you insist!{Gab}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.61,0:06:21.11,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Are they your crewmembers? - OG}Are those your men?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.69,0:06:24.16,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{That's quite a small group you got! - OG}{That's a pretty small crew\Nyou got there! - Gaijin}Don't you think\Nyour crew is a bit small?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.16,0:06:27.07,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{What're you saying?!\NI've got two more! - OG}What're you talking about?!\NWe have two more!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.07,0:06:29.04,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Hey! You counted me, didn't you?!{OG}{Hey, don't go counting me in! - Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.45,0:06:32.79,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,I'll deal with you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.33,0:06:36.29,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I'll go feed my underlings. - OG}{I'll go feed my men first. - Gaijin}I'm going to feed my men first.{Z - redundant "I'll" with previous line}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.96,0:06:44.01,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Those who don't want to die can\Nabandon the restaurant and escape. - OG}Anyone who wants to live\Nshould clear out before I get back.{Gaijin/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.76,0:06:49.18,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{All I'm after are the logbook and this ship. - OG}{I'm only after that ship's log and this ship. - Gaijin}I'm only after your\Nlogbook and this ship.{JT/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.93,0:06:54.69,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{But if you still wish to be uselessly killed... - OG}If you still want\Nto throw your life away,{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.69,0:06:57.86,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{...it's a bother, but I'll bury you into the sea. - OG}{I can spare the time\Nto bury you at sea! - Gaijin}I'll spare some time\Nto bury you at sea!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.36,0:06:59.98,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Know that. - OG}Make your choice.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.74,0:07:06.74,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I'm sorry, Sanji-san. - OG}I'm so sorry, Sanji.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.74,0:07:09.58,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I never imagined this would happen... - OG}{I had no idea he'd take it this far. - Gaijin}I had no idea he'd go this far.{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.58,0:07:13.41,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{That's not something you\Nshould apologize for, underling. - OG}You don't need to apologize, grunt.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.58,0:07:18.92,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Each cook at this restaurant acted\Nas they felt was right. - OG}Every cook here did\Nwhat they thought was right.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.92,0:07:21.00,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{That's all. - OG}That's all there is to it.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.00,0:07:22.38,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Owner! - OG}{Owner Zeff! - Gaijin}Chef Zeff!{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.38,0:07:27.01,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Why are you acting as\Nif you're taking Sanji's side?! - OG}You're not seriously taking\NSanji's side in this, are you?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.01,0:07:28.34,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.34,0:07:31.22,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{He's responsible for this whole thing! - OG}{He's the root of all of this! - Gaijin}It's his fault this happened!{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.72,0:07:34.77,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{He's going to put your precious\Nrestaurant out of business! - OG}He's trying to destroy\Nyour precious restaurant!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.77,0:07:36.56,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Shut up, you idiots! - OG}{Shut up, peabrains! - Gaijin}Shut up, you damn eggplants!{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.77,0:07:43.78,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Have you felt what it's like to\Nbe on the brink of starvation?! - OG}{Have you ever been so hungry\Nthat you thought you'd die?! - Gaijin}Have you ever felt such hunger\Nyou thought you'd die?!{Chloe}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.24,0:07:51.28,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Losing food and water on this grand ocean...\NDo you know how scary it is?! - OG}{[/q2]Do you know the terror of running out\Nof food and water on this vast ocean?! - Gaijin}{\q2}Can you comprehend the terror of running\Nout of food and water on this vast ocean?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.28,0:07:54.54,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Do you know how hard it is?! - OG}Can you comprehend such suffering?!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.54,0:07:55.41,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{What?! - OG}Huh?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.41,0:07:58.04,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{What do you mean, Owner? - OG}{What do you mean,\NOwner Zeff?! - Gaijin}Ch-Chef Zeff, what do you mean?{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.04,0:08:00.58,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{If you have time to grumble, - OG}{If you've got time to bitch and moan, - Gaijin}If all you're going to do\Nis bitch and moan,{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.58,0:08:03.55,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{leave the restaurant from the back door already! - OG}crawl out the back door and get lost!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.67,0:08:08.30,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,I'll stay and fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.30,0:08:11.47,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I couldn't bear it if I was just\Nbeaten and didn't fight back. - OG}I'm too pissed off to let\Nmyself get whupped like that!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.47,0:08:15.43,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I'll stay, too! This is the restaurant where I work! - OG}{Me too! This is where I work! - Gaijin}I'm staying too! This is\Nwhere I work after all!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.43,0:08:17.81,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{We don't have anywhere else to go anyway! - OG}{I got nowhere else to go. - Gaijin}We have nowhere else to go anyway!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.65,0:08:21.69,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{What do you think you're doing?! - OG}What are you doing?!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.69,0:08:24.65,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{You saw how powerful Don is, right?! - OG}You saw what the don is capable of!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.65,0:08:26.15,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Hey, Gin!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.57,0:08:28.11,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Let me tell you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.11,0:08:33.08,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Feeding someone who's hungry is my morality. - OG}My duty as a cook is to feed\Nthose who are hungry.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.08,0:08:33.87,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{But... - OG}That said...{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.66,0:08:42.04,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{...those we'll be dealing with\Nare plunderers with full bellies. - OG}when those looters\Nturn on me with full bellies...{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.79,0:08:47.63,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I won't let you complain even\Nwhen I beat up your fellow pirates. - OG}{I'll beat the hell out of them,\Neven if they[/i1]are[/i0]in your crew. That goes for you too. - Gaijin}I don't want to hear you complain\Nwhen I beat up your fellow pirates.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.63,0:08:49.55,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{If someone's going to take over this restaurant, - OG}Just try to take this restaurant,{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.88,0:08:53.26,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{even if it's you, I'll kill them without hesitation! - OG}and I'll kill you without\Na second thought.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.89,0:08:55.01,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Got that? - OG}Understood?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.22,0:09:01.65,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Letting him live and now killing him?\NYou're hopeless, Sanji... - OG}{Sanji, I can't believe you'd kill him\Nafter keeping him alive. - Gaijin}You'd kill him after saving his life?\NYou're hopeless, Sanji...{Z/PP/Chloe}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.65,0:09:03.06,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Shut up, you damn cook! - OG}Shut up, you crappy cook!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.44,0:09:05.69,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{You see? He's kinda cool, isn't he? - OG}{Look at that!\NHe's pretty cool, huh?! - Gaijin}See? He's pretty cool, huh?!{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.69,0:09:08.11,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Who cares about him?! - OG}{Whatever. I don't care about him. - Gaijin}That's nice, but enough about {\i1}him{\i0}!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.11,0:09:10.24,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{We'd better get out of here now! - OG}{We gotta get outta here! - Gaijin}{\i1}We{\i0} have to get out of here!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.24,0:09:11.16,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Calm down! - OG}Settle down!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.70,0:09:14.66,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Even if it's Krieg, he's a wreck with injuries. - OG}{Did you see Krieg?\NHe's worse for wear. - Gaijin}{Did you see Krieg? He's in bad shape. - JT}He may be Krieg,\Nbut he's in bad shape.{Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.66,0:09:20.33,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Ghin! You said you didn't know\Nanything about the Grand Line. - OG}Gin, you said you don't know anything\Nabout the Grand Line, didn't you?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.33,0:09:22.21,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Even though you've been there? - OG}{You've been there, right?! - Gaijin}But you've been there.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.33,0:09:25.67,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{It's still true that I don't know. - OG}{It's true; the Grand Line is a mystery to me. - Gaijin}I still don't know a thing\Nabout the Grand Line.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.13,0:09:30.34,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{What happened on the seventh day\Nafter we entered the Grand Line... - OG}What we saw on our\Nseventh day on the Grand Line...{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.34,0:09:32.01,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,I don't know if it was a dream...{OG}{might have been a dream... - Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.09,0:09:34.05,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,or reality...{OG}{or it might have been real. - Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.05,0:09:38.89,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I still haven't been able\Nto come to terms with it... - OG}I still can't wrap my head around it.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.85,0:09:41.64,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I still just can't believe... - OG}It was unbelievable!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.06,0:09:45.77,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{...that the 50-ship fleet... - OG}How could a lone man...{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.28,0:09:51.99,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{...was wiped out by only one man... - OG}destroy a fleet of fifty ships?!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.87,0:09:59.62,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{ - OG}– What?!\N– What?!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.41,0:10:04.25,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{It happened suddenly... - OG}It happened out of nowhere.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.25,0:10:07.63,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{\c&H060604&\3c&H060604&\4c&H060604&\t(18,1019,1,\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H000000&\4c&H000000&)}{As soon as this man appeared, - OG}Before we even realized he was there,{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.63,0:10:10.67,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{he sank the ships one after another. - OG}{the ships begin to sink one after another. - Gaijin}the ships began to sink,\None after another.{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.01,0:10:18.51,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{If we hadn't been lucky enough\Nto have that storm then, - OG}If we hadn't been lucky enough\Nto encounter that storm,{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.51,0:10:21.81,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{our main ship would've been\Ncompletely destroyed as well... - OG}our flagship would have\Nmet the same fate.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.48,0:10:33.57,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I don't know how many ships we have left... - OG}{I don't know how many\Nof our crew's ships survived. - Gaijin}I don't know how many\Nof our ships survived.{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.57,0:10:38.20,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{It was just so dreadful that I don't want to accept it as reality... - OG}{It's just too horrible\Nto accept that it was real. - Gaijin}It's just too horrible\Nto believe it was real.{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.20,0:10:40.16,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I don't want to remember... - OG}I want to forget what happened!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.16,0:10:42.91,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{...that man's... - OG}I want to forget that man—{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.91,0:10:46.83,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{...sharp, hawk-like eyes whose glare alone - OG}how he could seemingly kill\Nwith just a glance—{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.83,0:10:49.17,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{gives one the chill of death. - OG}with that hawk-like glare!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.80,0:10:50.80,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Wha... - OG}What?!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.80,0:10:51.55,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.67,0:10:54.47,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{What did he just say?! - OG}Could it be...?!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.18,0:11:00.26,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{That... - OG}There's no mistaking it.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.68,0:11:04.02,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{...must be Hawk-Eye... - OG}That must be the man\Nknown as Hawk Eye.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.02,0:11:04.89,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.44,0:11:11.36,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{That you felt his eyes were like\Na hawk's isn't proof in and of itself, - OG}{\q2}Just telling us that his eyes were like\Nthose of a hawk wouldn't be proof alone.{Gaijin/Gordy}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.36,0:11:17.49,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{but what this man did is\Nenough proof that it's him... - OG}{But the fact that he could commit\Nsomething so horrendous is plenty of evidence that it's him. - Gaijin}{\q2}But knowing he was capable of something\Nso devastating is plenty convincing for me.{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.95,0:11:19.83,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Hawk-Eye! - OG}The hawk-eyed man!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.83,0:11:22.16,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Huh? You know him, Zoro? - OG}Huh? Do you know him, Zoro?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.41,0:11:25.04,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.04,0:11:27.33,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{He's the man I'm looking for. - OG}It's who I've been looking for.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.42,0:11:33.34,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Isn't it possible that that man had\Nsome deep grudge towards you guys? - OG}{That guy must have really had\Na grudge against your crew. - Gaijin}{I'm guessing he had a serious\Ngrudge against your crew. - Z}Is it possible he had some sort\Nof grudge against your crew?{Chloe/Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.34,0:11:35.22,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{We never did anything to him! - OG}I'd never seen him before!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.22,0:11:38.01,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Like you guys disturbed his nap or something... - OG}Maybe you woke him\Nfrom a nap or something.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.01,0:11:39.64,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Don't be ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.64,0:11:42.89,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I'll be damned if he crushed\Nour fleet for such a reason! - OG}{Who the hell would\Nsmash a fleet over that?! - Gaijin}Who the hell smashes\Nan entire fleet over that?!{Chloe/Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.23,0:11:46.14,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Don't get so worked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.14,0:11:47.85,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,It's just an example.{OG}{I'm just saying... - Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.65,0:11:53.82,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I'm just giving an example of what \Nkind of place the Grand Line is. - OG}{that could be possible\Nin the Grand Line. - Gaijin}{that sort of thing is possible\Nin the Grand Line. - JT}That is, it's an example of what\Nkind of place the Grand Line is.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.82,0:11:56.45,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{What the heck kind of place is that? - OG}What kind of place is that?!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.45,0:11:59.20,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{It probably means that anything can happen. - OG}{It means anything could happen. - Gaijin}A place where anything could happen.{Gab}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.37,0:12:03.62,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Hey Luffy! Let's not go to a place like that! - OG}Hey Luffy, we shouldn't\Ngo somewhere like that!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.62,0:12:05.25,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Luffy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.25,0:12:10.17,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Hey, Luffy?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.54,0:12:13.92,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Ahhh! It sounds so exciting!! - OG}Whoa, that's so freaking cool!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.92,0:12:15.97,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{That's how it should be! - OG}I knew it had to be crazy there!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.97,0:12:18.51,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{You need to get the concept of\N"danger" into your thick skull! - OG}At least acknowledge\Nhow dangerous it is!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.51,0:12:23.26,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{But my goal is now completely\Nnarrowed down to the Grand Line. - OG}Well, that settles it. My only goal\Nat this point is the Grand Line.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.26,0:12:24.72,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.14,0:12:26.77,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{That man... - OG}I'll find him there...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.77,0:12:29.60,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I can see that man if I go there... - OG}{The Grand Line's\Nwhere I'm going to find him! - Gaijin}I'll find that man on the Grand Line!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.23,0:12:33.44,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Are you guys stupid or what? - OG}Are you nuts?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.15,0:12:36.61,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Guys like you die before anyone else. - OG}You're the type\Nto charge in and die first.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.99,0:12:40.45,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Yeah, but you didn't have to call us "stupid." - OG}{You're right, but you're going\Ntoo far to say I'm nuts. - Gaijin}You're right, but saying I'm "nuts" is going too far.{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.57,0:12:46.41,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{When I decided to become the strongest swordsman, I decided to devote my life to it. - OG}{I sacrificed myself when I decided\Nto be the world's best swordsman. - Gaijin}I threw my life away when I decided\Nto be the world's greatest swordsman.{JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.91,0:12:51.13,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Since it was my decision, the only\None who can call me stupid is me. - OG}Only one person can call me nuts,\Nand that person is me!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.29,0:12:55.63,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Ahh! Me too, me too! - OG}Yeah, the same goes for me!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.63,0:12:58.38,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Me, too! That's just natural as a man of the sea! - OG}{Yeah, me too! I'm a man of the sea! - Gaijin}Yeah, me too, since I'm\Na man of the sea and all!{Chloe/Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.38,0:13:00.09,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,In your case, that's a lie.{OG}{You're lying. - Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.55,0:13:04.31,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{What nonsense... - OG}{How ridiculous... - Gaijin}Ridiculous...{Gab}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.73,0:13:09.73,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Hey! - OG}Hey, hey!{Gaijin}{Alrighty then! - Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.73,0:13:13.73,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Do you idiots understand the current situation?! - OG}Do you numbskulls have any idea\Nwhat's going on here?!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.73,0:13:20.95,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{The ship moored in front of the restaurant is the huge Galleon that belongs to Don Krieg, Commodore of the "pirate fleet"! - OG}{\q2}Outside this restaurant is a massive galleon\Nfrom Pirate Commodore Don Krieg's fleet!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.95,0:13:25.03,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{If you wanna escape from reality, do it after surviving this life-or-death crisis! - OG}You can build your castles in the sky\Nwhen the battle is over!{Gaijin}{You can dream all you want\Nwhen the battle is over! - JT}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.17,0:13:36.55,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,– We're saved!\N– We're saved!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.55,0:13:38.30,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Great! We're still alive! - OG}{I'm so glad we're gonna live! - Gaijin}This is great! We're gonna live!{Z/Chloe}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.30,0:13:39.84,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{It seems like a dream! - OG}It's like I'm dreaming!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.84,0:13:42.51,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,We're free from that nightmare!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.51,0:13:46.97,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{We came back alive from the pirate graveyard! - OG}We made it back alive\Nfrom the Pirate Graveyard!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.06,0:13:50.14,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.89,0:13:55.23,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{which means that we can now\Nhead to the Grand Line again. - OG}We can once again turn\Nour sights on the Grand Line.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.90,0:13:59.36,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.36,0:14:00.99,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{What's with those faces? - OG}What's with those looks?{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.57,0:14:03.91,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{A-Are we going to that place again? - OG}W-We're going back there?!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.83,0:14:13.58,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{No more objections, right? - OG}{Anybody else have any objections? - Gaijin}Any other objections?{Gab}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.55,0:14:26.80,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,First,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.35,0:14:32.52,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{abandon this wrecked ship that could sink at any moment and take over the restaurant. - OG}we'll abandon this irreparable wreck\Nand take over the restaurant.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.52,0:14:35.69,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Our enemy's just some punk cooks. - OG}{It's staffed by a gang\Nof thuggish cooks. - Gaijin}Our enemy is a staff of punk cooks.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.69,0:14:38.27,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Even if you take your opponent lightly,\Nthat's still more than enough... - OG}They've got nothing on us.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.49,0:14:45.78,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.25,0:14:53.71,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Here they come!\NWe can hear their war cry! - OG}They're coming!\NI can hear them yelling!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.71,0:14:57.75,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{We'll protect the ship to the end!\NIt's our restaurant! - OG}{Hold them off!\NThis ship is our restaurant! - Gaijin}Hold them off! This ship—\Nthis restaurant is ours!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.38,0:15:03.13,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Out of our way, cooks! - OG}Make way, you scum!{Gaijin}
